5be8b448b5a3755a29e%2Fap25264133918049.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4554x2562+0+237/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F62%2F60%2Fa5bd37de45be8b448b5a3755a29e%2Fap25264133918049.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4554x2562+0+237/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F62%2F60%2Fa5bd37de45be8b448b5a3755a29e%2Fap25264133918049.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4554x2562+0+237/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F62%2F60%2Fa5bd37de45be8b448b5a3755a29e%2Fap25264133918049.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4554x2562+0+237/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F62%2F60%2Fa5bd37de45be8b448b5a3755a29e%2Fap25264133918049.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4554x2562+0+237/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F62%2F60%2Fa5bd37de45be8b448b5a3755a29e%2Fap25264133918049.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4554x2562+0+237/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F62%2F60%2Fa5bd37de45be8b448b5a3755a29e%2Fap25264133918049.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4554x2562+0+237/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F62%2F60%2Fa5bd37de45be8b448b5a3755a29e%2Fap25264133918049.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4554x2562+0+237/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F62%2F60%2Fa5bd37de45be8b448b5a3755a29e%2Fap25264133918049.jpg" class="img" alt="Bad Bunny performs during the final concert of his summer residency in his homeland at the Coliseo de Puerto Rico Jose Miguel Agrelot, in San Juan, Puerto Rico, Saturday, Sept. 20, 2025." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Bad Bunny performs during the final concert of his summer residency in his homeland at the Coliseo de Puerto Rico Jose Miguel Agrelot, in San Juan, Puerto Rico, Saturday, Sept. 20, 2025.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Alejandro Granadillo/AP                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Puerto Rican rapper and singer Bad Bunny will &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/09/29/nx-s1-5556772/latin-superstar-bad-bunny-will-headline-the-2026-super-bowl-halftime-show" target="_blank"&gt;headline the Super Bowl 60 halftime show&lt;/a&gt; on Feb. 8. The NFL announced the performance during last night's Green Bay Packers and Dallas Cowboys game.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;National Coming Out Day is celebrated on Oct. 11 to recognize the courage of LGBTQ+ individuals who come out publicly. This year, NPR is inviting people to share their coming out stories. &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/09/26/g-s1-90442/lgbtq-national-coming-out-day" target="_blank"&gt;Your submission could be featured&lt;/a&gt; in an upcoming edition of &lt;em&gt;this&lt;/em&gt; newsletter.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Actress and comedian Heather McMahan &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/09/28/nx-s1-5555995/ryder-cup-emcee-jeering-fans" target="_blank"&gt;stepped down as emcee for the Ryder Cup&lt;/a&gt; after she was heard heckling and cursing at golfers during the championship game over the weekend.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/g-s1-2467/obed-manuel"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Obed Manuel&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
