      <description>&lt;div id="storytext" class="storytext storylocation linkLocation"&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Good morning. You're reading the Up First newsletter. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/newsletter/news" target="_blank"&gt;Subscribe&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; here to get it delivered to your inbox, and &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/podcasts/510318/up-first/" target="_blank"&gt;listen&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; to the Up First podcast for all the news you need to start your day.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Today's top stories&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A grand jury in Virginia has indicted former FBI Director James Comey on charges of obstructing justice and making a false statement to Congress.&lt;/strong&gt; The charges come after President Trump demanded prosecutors pick up the pace in building a case against one of his most prominent critics. The &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/09/25/nx-s1-5552690/james-comey-indicted" target="_blank"&gt;president has targeted Comey for years&lt;/a&gt;, blaming him for the appointment of a special prosecutor who probed connections between Russia and Trump's 2016 campaign through much of his first term in office.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-90373" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 4658;         --source-height: 2620;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4658x2620+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9e%2F6a%2Fc807cd494a138b09bfc0b5e3d484%2Fgettyimages-1078705736.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4658x2620+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9e%2F6a%2Fc807cd494a138b09bfc0b5e3d484%2Fgettyimages-1078705736.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4658x2620+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9e%2F6a%2Fc807cd494a138b09bfc0b5e3d484%2Fgettyimages-1078705736.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4658x2620+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9e%2F6a%2Fc807cd494a138b09bfc0b5e3d484%2Fgettyimages-1078705736.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4658x2620+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9e%2F6a%2Fc807cd494a138b09bfc0b5e3d484%2Fgettyimages-1078705736.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4658x2620+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9e%2F6a%2Fc807cd494a138b09bfc0b5e3d484%2Fgettyimages-1078705736.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4658x2620+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9e%2F6a%2Fc807cd494a138b09bfc0b5e3d484%2Fgettyimages-1078705736.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4658x2620+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9e%2F6a%2Fc807cd494a138b09bfc0b5e3d484%2Fgettyimages-1078705736.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4658x2620+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9e%2F6a%2Fc807cd494a138b09bfc0b5e3d484%2Fgettyimages-1078705736.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4658x2620+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9e%2F6a%2Fc807cd494a138b09bfc0b5e3d484%2Fgettyimages-1078705736.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4658x2620+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9e%2F6a%2Fc807cd494a138b09bfc0b5e3d484%2Fgettyimages-1078705736.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4658x2620+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9e%2F6a%2Fc807cd494a138b09bfc0b5e3d484%2Fgettyimages-1078705736.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4658x2620+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9e%2F6a%2Fc807cd494a138b09bfc0b5e3d484%2Fgettyimages-1078705736.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4658x2620+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9e%2F6a%2Fc807cd494a138b09bfc0b5e3d484%2Fgettyimages-1078705736.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4658x2620+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9e%2F6a%2Fc807cd494a138b09bfc0b5e3d484%2Fgettyimages-1078705736.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4658x2620+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9e%2F6a%2Fc807cd494a138b09bfc0b5e3d484%2Fgettyimages-1078705736.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4658x2620+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9e%2F6a%2Fc807cd494a138b09bfc0b5e3d484%2Fgettyimages-1078705736.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4658x2620+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9e%2F6a%2Fc807cd494a138b09bfc0b5e3d484%2Fgettyimages-1078705736.jpg" class="img" alt="Former Federal Bureau of Investigation Director James Comey leaves the Rayburn House Office Building after testifying to two House committees on Dec. 7, 2018, in Washington, D.C." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Former Federal Bureau of Investigation Director James Comey leaves the Rayburn House Office Building after testifying to two House committees on Dec. 7, 2018, in Washington, D.C.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Chip Somodevilla/Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧 &lt;strong&gt;NPR's Carrie Johnson tells &lt;em&gt;Up First&lt;/em&gt; it's a "bare bones" indictment, coming in at only two full pages.&lt;/strong&gt; However, Trump said Comey is at the beginning of being held responsible for his crimes. Last week, the White House forced out a career prosecutor who raised doubts about the strength of evidence in the Comey case. Lindsey Halligan, an insurance lawyer with no prosecutor experience, was then ushered into the role. The Justice Department &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=nx-s1-5554175:nx-s1-mx-5734656" target="_blank"&gt;must demonstrate that Comey knowingly lied&lt;/a&gt; about a significant matter for the charges to be upheld. Johnson says Comey may be able to argue that he is being prosecuted out of vindictiveness, given the president's remarks.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth yesterday summoned the Pentagon's top commanders &lt;/strong&gt;from around the world to a meeting in Virginia next week. The Pentagon has not released why the unusual gathering was called or what the plans are. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🎧 &lt;strong&gt;NPR Pentagon correspondent Tom Bowman says he hasn't heard of anything on this scale happening before.&lt;/strong&gt; He says, at times, the Pentagon has brought in combatant commanders, who oversee military operations around the world, for annual meetings. But this is very different in numbers. Hegseth discussed reducing the number of admirals and generals during his confirmation. Bowman says this &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=nx-s1-5554175:nx-s1-mx-5734656" target="_blank"&gt;could be the reason&lt;/a&gt; for the meeting, but that isn't known for sure.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The U.S. government plans to collect a multibillion-dollar fee from the American investors set to take over TikTok's U.S. operations.&lt;/strong&gt; The Trump administration recently approached the investors, who include tech mogul Larry Ellison and the Murdochs, to inquire if they would make a payment to the federal government in "in the low billions," according to a person with direct knowledge of the talks. Their response was an unequivocal yes. Some experts call the fee and other &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/09/26/g-s1-90598/tiktok-deal-trump-oracle" target="_blank"&gt;deals like it "extortion."&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Picture show&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-89018" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 2400;         --source-height: 1350;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2400x1350+0+291/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff0%2F44%2F1546e02f4590b2bc7aacf5a3e4d8%2F081625-sallymann-458-2.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2400x1350+0+291/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff0%2F44%2F1546e02f4590b2bc7aacf5a3e4d8%2F081625-sallymann-458-2.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2400x1350+0+291/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff0%2F44%2F1546e02f4590b2bc7aacf5a3e4d8%2F081625-sallymann-458-2.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2400x1350+0+291/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff0%2F44%2F1546e02f4590b2bc7aacf5a3e4d8%2F081625-sallymann-458-2.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2400x1350+0+291/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff0%2F44%2F1546e02f4590b2bc7aacf5a3e4d8%2F081625-sallymann-458-2.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2400x1350+0+291/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff0%2F44%2F1546e02f4590b2bc7aacf5a3e4d8%2F081625-sallymann-458-2.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2400x1350+0+291/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff0%2F44%2F1546e02f4590b2bc7aacf5a3e4d8%2F081625-sallymann-458-2.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2400x1350+0+291/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff0%2F44%2F1546e02f4590b2bc7aacf5a3e4d8%2F081625-sallymann-458-2.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2400x1350+0+291/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff0%2F44%2F1546e02f4590b2bc7aacf5a3e4d8%2F081625-sallymann-458-2.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2400x1350+0+291/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff0%2F44%2F1546e02f4590b2bc7aacf5a3e4d8%2F081625-sallymann-458-2.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2400x1350+0+291/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff0%2F44%2F1546e02f4590b2bc7aacf5a3e4d8%2F081625-sallymann-458-2.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2400x1350+0+291/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff0%2F44%2F1546e02f4590b2bc7aacf5a3e4d8%2F081625-sallymann-458-2.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2400x1350+0+291/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff0%2F44%2F1546e02f4590b2bc7aacf5a3e4d8%2F081625-sallymann-458-2.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2400x1350+0+291/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff0%2F44%2F1546e02f4590b2bc7aacf5a3e4d8%2F081625-sallymann-458-2.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2400x1350+0+291/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff0%2F44%2F1546e02f4590b2bc7aacf5a3e4d8%2F081625-sallymann-458-2.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2400x1350+0+291/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff0%2F44%2F1546e02f4590b2bc7aacf5a3e4d8%2F081625-sallymann-458-2.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2400x1350+0+291/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff0%2F44%2F1546e02f4590b2bc7aacf5a3e4d8%2F081625-sallymann-458-2.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2400x1350+0+291/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Ff0%2F44%2F1546e02f4590b2bc7aacf5a3e4d8%2F081625-sallymann-458-2.jpg" class="img" alt="Sally Mann in her home studio in Virginia on August 16, 2025." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Sally Mann in her home studio in Virginia on August 16, 2025.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Zayrha Rodriguez/NPR                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Works from photographer Sally Mann can be seen at major art institutions around the world. But this year, police seized four of her most celebrated photographs. In one, a toddler is asleep, sprawled across a bed she wetted, and in another, a popsicle drips on her son's lower body, genitals included. The images are part of her &lt;em&gt;Immediate Family&lt;/em&gt; series that has been displayed for over 30 years. The Danbury Institute, a conservative Christian advocacy group, accused the Modern Art Museum of Fort Worth in Texas of displaying "child pornography" in a December 2024 open letter, which was backed by local elected officials. Mann anticipates there will be more attacks on art by people who don't understand the works they are vilifying. Read more about what Mann says is a "&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/09/24/nx-s1-5350583/art-work-sally-mann" target="_blank"&gt;new era of culture wars&lt;/a&gt;" and see &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/09/24/nx-s1-5350583/art-work-sally-mann" target="_blank"&gt;photos of some of Mann's works&lt;/a&gt; throughout the years. Listen to &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=nx-s1-5350583:x" target="_blank"&gt;what she has to say&lt;/a&gt; about the seizure of her art or &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/transcripts/nx-s1-5350583" target="_blank"&gt;read the transcript&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Weekend picks&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-89918" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 2000;         --source-height: 1124;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1124+0+47/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F28%2Fd7%2F6b88b48442578896e8f34e68f5b4%2Fdf-07499-r-2000x1333-thumbnail.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1124+0+47/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F28%2Fd7%2F6b88b48442578896e8f34e68f5b4%2Fdf-07499-r-2000x1333-thumbnail.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1124+0+47/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F28%2Fd7%2F6b88b48442578896e8f34e68f5b4%2Fdf-07499-r-2000x1333-thumbnail.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2000x1124+0+47/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F28%2Fd7%2F6b88b48442578896e8f34e68f5b4%2Fdf-07499-r-2000x13